metamod/MM2" name="software_version">twv_algo3.pro V1.0</metadata><metadata xmlns="http://www.met.no/schema/metamod/MM2" name="datacollection_period_to">2006-04-30</metadata><metadata xmlns="http://www.met.no/schema/metamod/MM2" name="title">Total Water Vapour derived from AMSU-B</metadata><metadata xmlns="http://www.met.no/schema/metamod/MM2" name="abstract">
Daily total water vapor (TWV) derived from radiances (five channels)
measured 
by the microwave instrument AMSU-B on the polar-orbiting
satellites NOAA-16 and 
17. For TWV less then about 7 kg/m2, the
retrieval works over any surface (land, 
open sea, sea ice). For TWV
above about 7 kg/m2, the retrieval works over sea 
ice only, for TWV
above 20 kg/m2, the retrieval fails over all surfaces. About 
14 daily
satellite passes, in the Arctic, each point is covered at least 
twice
daily. All satellite passes of one day are interpolated and averaged
onto 
a half-degree grid, using the "nearneighor" routine of the
Generic Mapping Tools 
(GMT) using four sectors and a searchradius of
60km.
